    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                <pb facs="nei.n1a.10.43-44"/>
                <fw type="curatorial">43</fw>
                <fw type="authorial"></fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        3305  
                        Omaha 68144 Neb. 
                        April 28, 1971
                    </dateline>
                    
                    <salute>Dear Dr. Neiahrdt.</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>The finest program I've ever seen and heard on TV was Dick Cavett's last night. You were and are superb. My husband, children and grandchildren all loved it: I hope Channel 7 will do a</p>
                
                <pb facs="nei.n1a.10.43-44"/>
                <fw type="curatorial">44</fw>
                <fw type="authorial"></fw>
                
                <p>repeat of it soon.</p> 
                <p>I've always loved your poetry but I also love the way you give it, your wisdom, your humanity, your strength, your sense of humor and common sense, your closeness to nature and to God - all of this and more - you breathed into your short one hour (minus commericals)</p> 
                <p>You have dwarfed</p>
                
                <pb facs="nei.n1a.10.43-44"/>
                <fw type="curatorial"></fw>
                <fw type="authorial"></fw>
                
                <p>anyone who has ever been on TV including Mr. Fost.</p> 
                <p>I hope you have done some recordings on records that we may buy.</p> 
                <p>Thank you for a memorable evening.</p> 
                <p>My ninety year old mother-in-law was thrilled, too.</p> 
                
                <closer>
                    <salute>Sincerely,</salute> 
                    <signed>Doris Pinkerton Madhem</signed> 

                </closer>
            </div1>
